oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Greenback Produce Co. Packing House
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Edwin Best
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Greenback (Tenn.);
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Several firms at various times trafficked in fresh produce, poultry, eggs, butter, tallow, hides, fruit, honey and other products of farm, field or forest. The packing house of the Greenback Produce Co. was built in 1903 and burned in 1917 (see also Brick Buildings 1917- 1918).
